    "body": "- `nvim --version`: v0.5.0-dev+967-g7afd4526f\r\n- `vim -u DEFAULTS` (version: ) behaves differently? Not applicable, as there is no `msgsep` flag\r\n- Operating system/version: Ubuntu 20.04.1\r\n- Terminal name/version: Konsole\r\n- `$TERM`: xterm-256color\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce using `nvim -u NORC`\r\n\r\n```\r\nnvim -u NORC\r\n```\r\n\r\nRemove the `msgsep` flag from the `'display'` option.\r\n\r\n```\r\n:set display-=msgsep\r\n```\r\n\r\nSource the following script, which will create a floating window at the bottom of the screen.\r\n\r\n```\r\n\" script.vim\r\nlet buf = nvim_create_buf(v:false, v:true)\r\ncall nvim_buf_set_lines(buf, 0, -1, v:true, ['test', 'text'])\r\nlet opts = {\r\n      \\   'relative': 'editor',\r\n      \\   'width': 30,\r\n      \\   'height': 2,\r\n      \\   'col': 0,\r\n      \\   'row': 9999,\r\n      \\   'anchor': 'NW',\r\n      \\   'style': 'minimal'\r\n      \\ }\r\nlet win = nvim_open_win(buf, 0, opts)\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\n:source /path/to/script.vim\r\n```\r\n\r\nThrow an error to receive a multi-line message.\r\n\r\n```\r\n:throw 'error'\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nThe floating window covers the message.\r\n\r\n![message_covered](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/541289/103143845-dc77d880-46ec-11eb-8085-bfa54f2dcce7.png)\r\n\r\n### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nThe message covers the floating window.\r\n\r\n`msgsep` was included in `'display'` for the purpose of generating the following image, so the image does not properly reflect the expected behaviour across the entire screen, but is intended to show the expectation that the messages should cover the floating window.\r\n\r\n![float_covered](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/541289/103143849-e994c780-46ec-11eb-9b23-8d10253819d7.png)",
